birthweight_data %>% 
  cor_mat() %>%
  cor_gather() %>%
  filter(var1 %in% "bwt") %>%
  filter(!var2 %in% "bwt") %>%
  mutate(
    sig_p = ifelse(p < 0.01, T, F),
    cor_if_sig = ifelse(p < 0.01, cor, NA)
    ) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(
    x = var1, 
    y = var2, 
    fill = cor,
    label = round(cor_if_sig, 2))) + 
  geom_tile(color = "white") +   
  geom_text(
    color = "white",
    size = 4
  ) + 
  scale_x_discrete(
    labels = c("Birth Weight")
  ) + 
  labs(
    x = "Outcome Variable",
    y = "Predictor Variables",
    title = "Correlation Matrix between Predictors and Outcome",
    subtitle = "significant predictors at significance level 0.01",
    fill = "Correlation"
  )

variables <-  
  cleaned_birthweight_data %>%
  select(-bwt) %>%
  select_if(is.numeric) %>%
  colnames() %>% 
  as.list()
for (i in variables){
  plot <-
   ggplot(birthweight_data, aes_string(i,  "bwt")) + 
   geom_point() +
   geom_smooth(method = lm, se = FALSE)
  print(plot)
}
